text: If a student loses or damages their ID card, or if it becomes unusable for any reason, they should fill out the replacement request form by following this link: https://docs.google.com/forms/d/16Gx6EdDWwJXH_SmCKbCVnrj2n5eaf9T9B4CdsplNhfw/edit .Once submitted, a new ID card will be issued within the next few days.

To access various services such as course registration, viewing your advisor information, checking the system calendar, accessing your curriculum, viewing attendance, submitting course consent requests, registering for upcoming courses, adding courses to your wish list, withdrawing from courses, finding curriculum information, accessing transcripts, viewing current grades, checking your course schedule, accessing financial or accounting information, viewing electronic attendance records, accessing the system calendar for important dates, checking gate entry records, finding student rules and regulations, accessing university messages, and participating in university surveys, please log into your account at the following link: https://oldmy.sdu.edu.kz/

To approve your Health Statement, you can fill out the online approval form. Simply follow this link to submit your information: https://docs.google.com/forms/d/19qN_q9ZgkgE-Xm-13QxJgQp81PB7PAHVZoP9UZRKQ7g/edit .This form allows for Health Statement approval without needing to visit the campus.

To apply for an academic leave or an academic break, please complete the request form by providing your reasons. You can access the form through this link: https://docs.google.com/forms/d/1xR-D4GcX5k6KFLMVxeA8tjiG8PefCVZlB9PAqaeTUqE/edit .This form allows students to request academic leave or breaks conveniently online.

If you are a graduate and need to retrieve archival information or an academic transcript, please complete the request form available at the following link: https://docs.google.com/forms/d/1E7MU7LeDv2Xd6p-lSe7I_WLwCky5fiKPPJRIZZbZpOc/edit .You can expect a response within a few days after submission.

You can pay your university tuition fees online through either Kaspi Bank or Halyk Bank. For Kaspi Bank, use this link: https://kaspi.kz/pay/_gate?action=service_with_subservice&service_id=2766&subservice_id=8180&region_id=18 .For Halyk Bank, use this link: https://homebank.kz/payments/sduUniversitetImeniSulejmanaDemirelya

If you need to change or update the WiFi settings for Moodle-SDU, please refer to the detailed instructions available in this guide: https://helpdesk.sdu.edu.kz/knowledgebase.php?article=4 .This article provides step-by-step guidance for modifying your WiFi configuration.

To change or reset your SDU email password, please refer to the step-by-step instructions provided in this guide: https://helpdesk.sdu.edu.kz/knowledgebase.php?article=6 .This article will walk you through the process of updating your password.

To configure the Gmail app to use your SDU email on your phone, please follow the detailed instructions in this guide: https://helpdesk.sdu.edu.kz/knowledgebase.php?article=8 .This article provides a step-by-step setup process for integrating your SDU email with the Gmail app.

To enable the 'Undo Send' option in your SDU email or to request a change in your academic specialty, please refer to the instructions provided in this guide: https://helpdesk.sdu.edu.kz/knowledgebase.php?article=11 .This article offers detailed steps for both actions.

If you wish to withdraw from the university, please complete the withdrawal form at this link: https://docs.google.com/forms/d/1rG0JGMxIuxh74y_MtVmk1XONVvaoOxh4fACwo85_kRU/viewform?edit_requested=true .This will initiate the formal process for ending your enrollment.

If you have completed similar courses in high school or college, you may be eligible for a price equalization to recognize those credits at SDU. To apply, please complete this form: https://docs.google.com/forms/d/1OXc7RPSkvTpjsvXEYRLZ8EetAsy9SMvKGa2gYcXNSWE/edit

If you need to request a refund for tuition, missed exams, course materials, or other university-related fees, please complete the refund request form here: https://docs.google.com/forms/d/1mc3DoenIw1qciVrJPeH_q2FdyXWsvt8NLFDSviehIL4/edit .This form will allow you to initiate the refund process.

If you need to restore, verify, or reissue your diploma, you can do so through the eGov platform. This online service allows you to manage diploma information without visiting the university. Here’s the link: https://egov.kz/
